## 3. Implementation Steps

For each file listed above:
1.  **Copy the core layout** structure from the monolithic [DashboardPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Windows%2010%20Lite/Downloads/MUNJOR/BPM/SYSTEM/SYSTEM%20OFFICIAL/BPM.2.0/src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx) (`<div className="px-4 py-4...">`).
2.  **Hardcode the specific role context** statically into the page. E.g., Move the specific `DASHBOARD_DATA[role]` objects to be static `const KPI_DATA = [...]` inside that file.
3.  **Import only required components.** E.g., Only import `PieChart` into the helpdesk dashboard, and `AreaChart` into the cemetery dashboard.
4.  **Remove conditional logic.** Since each file belongs to a specific role, checks like `if (user.role === 'treasurer')` will be removed.
5.  **Remove monolithic DashboardPage.** After migrating all dashboards, [src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Windows%2010%20Lite/Downloads/MUNJOR/BPM/SYSTEM/SYSTEM%20OFFICIAL/BPM.2.0/src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx) will be refactored to simply act as a conditional `Navigate` redirect (e.g., `if (user.role === 'cemetery') return <Navigate to="/cemetery/dashboard" />`).
